Why a stricter License in this Fork?
------------------------------------

The eegfaktura suite as a whole is operated as a network service and the
maintainers consider AGPL-3.0's §13 network-use clause important for
ensuring that all operators of derived services make their corresponding
source available to users. The other eegfaktura components are already
AGPL-3.0; this fork brings the backend into alignment with the rest of
the suite.

LGPL-2.1 §3 explicitly permits the recipient of LGPL-2.1 code to convert
their copy to the ordinary GNU General Public License. From there,
combination with AGPL-3.0 is permitted under the FSF license-compatibility
chain. This fork exercises that option for its distribution. Original
authorship and copyright of all contributors to the upstream
LGPL-2.1 codebase remain unaffected — only the distribution terms used by
this fork are stricter.

Upstream `eegfaktura/eegfaktura-backend` is **not** affected by this
relicensing. It remains LGPL-2.1; the present change applies only to the
fork distributed from this repository onward.


